messages.message: Thanks for that Loc. Based on this, I believe we should revert back to 0.560 and once we have time to remedy why 0.600 gives us so many pdb exceptions, we shouldn't upgrade to it

I've been running into a bunch of issues as well while coding, and realizing that 0.600 doesn't work great when we have syntax errors, whereas 0.560 for some reason handles them more gracefully and reports them back instead of giving us back a pdb exception
